1
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:12,000
<i>If you just agreed
to be the muse,</i>

2
00:00:12,133 --> 00:00:14,033
<i>you would be able
to get close to Amo.</i>

3
00:00:14,167 --> 00:00:15,200
<i> Sergeant Enriquez?</i>

4
00:00:15,333 --> 00:00:18,067
<i>Do you remember what we talked
about last time?</i>

5
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:21,067
<i>Including the poison used
on the kidnapper.</i>

6
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:23,233
<i>We have some toxic
plants here,</i>

7
00:00:23,367 --> 00:00:26,067
<i>but we haven't been housing
strychnine for a long time.</i>

8
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:28,000
<i> It's the same in your movies.</i>

9
00:00:28,133 --> 00:00:31,233
<i>But those criminals are
my super fans,</i>

10
00:00:31,367 --> 00:00:33,733
<i> maybe it's just a coincidence.</i>

11
00:00:33,900 --> 00:00:36,200
<i>Maybe you have contact with
someone where we can get poison.</i>

12
00:00:36,333 --> 00:00:37,533
<i>It depends on the poison, Boss.</i>

13
00:00:37,667 --> 00:00:39,967
<i>But they say there will be a
gang war in the basketball game.</i>

14
00:00:40,100 --> 00:00:41,100
<i> Oh, man!</i>

15
00:00:41,233 --> 00:00:43,533
<i>- You have the trophy.
- You're so arrogant!</i>

16
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:46,500
<i> Help!</i>

17
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:50,533
<i> Enriquez, are you okay?</i>

18
00:00:50,667 --> 00:00:51,467
<i> Okay, Sir.</i>

19
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:52,467
<i> That's four.</i>

20
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:53,767
<i> Three for me, one for you.</i>

21
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:56,500
<i> The other three are mine.</i>

22
00:00:56,633 --> 00:00:57,267
<i> Don't come any closer!</i>

23
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:58,333
<i> I'll kill him!</i>

24
00:00:58,467 --> 00:00:59,433
<i> Why? What's going on?</i>

25
00:00:59,567 --> 00:01:01,633
<i>They say a gang leader hostage
someone.</i>

26
00:01:01,767 --> 00:01:02,933
<i> Stay here.</i>

27
00:01:03,067 --> 00:01:06,433
<i>Get a car so we can escape
from here or we'll kill him!</i>

28
00:01:06,567 --> 00:01:07,700
<i> Wait, wait!</i>

29
00:01:13,533 --> 00:01:14,567
Close the door.

30
00:01:18,767 --> 00:01:19,667
Move over.

31
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:24,400
Okay.

32
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:28,033
Conde.

33
00:01:28,167 --> 00:01:28,633
Sir.

34
00:01:28,767 --> 00:01:29,567
What happened there?

35
00:01:30,833 --> 00:01:32,167
Someone was hostage inside.

36
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:35,933
Dizon, Robles, set the perimeter

37
00:01:36,067 --> 00:01:38,567
and just make sure that we have
the entire area under control,

38
00:01:38,700 --> 00:01:40,833
and our mission,
no one else gets hurt.

39
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:41,767
- Go ahead.
- Okay.

40
00:01:41,900 --> 00:01:43,433
Sir.

41
00:01:43,567 --> 00:01:44,200
Garcia.

42
00:01:45,900 --> 00:01:48,433
Six people, Sir, including their
gang leader.

43
00:01:48,567 --> 00:01:49,867
Has the leader been identified?

44
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,167
Chief,

45
00:01:51,300 --> 00:01:54,733
this group I'm talking to says
their leader's name is Daga.

46
00:01:54,867 --> 00:01:57,200
We need to get Daga's track
record.

47
00:01:57,333 --> 00:02:00,000
Garcia, call the office.

48
00:02:00,133 --> 00:02:01,200
Yes, Sir.

49
00:02:01,333 --> 00:02:03,900
Conde, do we have any contact
with them?

50
00:02:04,933 --> 00:02:08,067
None yet, Sir, but I'll try
to talk to him.

51
00:02:09,267 --> 00:02:11,800
Daga, the other police officers
have arrived.

52
00:02:13,067 --> 00:02:13,967
Wait a minute.

53
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:15,600
Come here!

54
00:02:15,767 --> 00:02:17,167
Stay there.

55
00:02:17,300 --> 00:02:18,267
Open it.

56
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:26,267
Good day to you, Daga!

57
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:28,733
I'm Tonyo from station 12.

58
00:02:28,867 --> 00:02:33,067
I want you to know,
if you need anything at all,

59
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:35,667
just talk to us.

60
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:38,433
I don't talk to pigs!

61
00:02:43,533 --> 00:02:45,333
Who do you want to talk to?

62
00:02:45,467 --> 00:02:46,500
Maybe I can help you.

63
00:02:46,633 --> 00:02:47,933
You're stubborn, aren't you?

64
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:49,267
You want me to kill this?

65
00:02:51,533 --> 00:02:55,900
That's enough, he might do it.

66
00:02:56,033 --> 00:02:57,667
You know those guys,
they have nothing to lose.

67
00:03:05,700 --> 00:03:06,767
- Major.
- Mr. Victor.

68
00:03:08,033 --> 00:03:09,900
What's going on here?

69
00:03:10,033 --> 00:03:11,233
There's a hostage-taking.

70
00:03:17,567 --> 00:03:20,133
Look, Pogi has also gone quiet.

71
00:03:21,633 --> 00:03:24,200
Maybe I can help.
I'll try to talk to them.

72
00:03:57,967 --> 00:03:58,533
Grandfather,

73
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:02,367
your granddaughter looks
beautiful.

74
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:09,700
Don't worry, Grandfather,
we will not hurt you.

75
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:14,667
We just happened to cross paths
with you.

76
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:21,400
Just pray that they give us
everything we want

77
00:04:23,133 --> 00:04:27,633
so that we won't end up
like this, right?

78
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,367
Sir Victor, I'm sorry.

79
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:32,900
We won't let a civilian
get hurt.

80
00:04:33,033 --> 00:04:34,400
We'll take care of this, Sir.

81
00:04:35,433 --> 00:04:38,200
Daga, it's Amo.
Isn't he your idol?

82
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:40,533
Yes, I've watched all of his
movies.

83
00:04:45,267 --> 00:04:45,933
I understand.

84
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:49,433
I'm only in the car
when you need something.

85
00:04:49,567 --> 00:04:50,600
Okay, Sir Victor.

86
00:04:50,733 --> 00:04:51,400
Amo?

87
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:54,633
Is that you?

88
00:04:54,767 --> 00:04:56,067
What are you doing here?

89
00:05:11,933 --> 00:05:12,667
Buddy,

90
00:05:13,933 --> 00:05:15,367
can I talk to you?

91
00:05:16,467 --> 00:05:17,867
As long as it's you, Amo!

92
00:05:19,533 --> 00:05:21,433
You're very welcome here.

93
00:05:21,567 --> 00:05:23,667
Just don't bring those police
officers with you.

94
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:28,000
But don't hurt your hostages
there.

95
00:05:28,133 --> 00:05:30,800
Let's just talk about
what your demands are.

96
00:05:30,933 --> 00:05:32,767
Sure, Amo!

97
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:34,767
As long as those police officers
stay there.

98
00:05:36,367 --> 00:05:38,900
Major, allow me to go in.

99
00:05:39,033 --> 00:05:42,467
Maybe we can save the hostages
more easily.

100
00:05:43,900 --> 00:05:44,933
Oh, okay.

101
00:05:45,067 --> 00:05:46,233
I'm coming in.

102
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:47,967
Give me, Grandfather.

103
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:49,333
Give me, Grandfather!

104
00:05:49,467 --> 00:05:52,167
- Let's go!
- Come on.

105
00:05:52,300 --> 00:05:52,933
Open it.

106
00:05:54,433 --> 00:05:55,300
Come on, come on.

107
00:05:57,567 --> 00:05:58,467
Open the gate.

108
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:07,867
Get Amo.

109
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:12,033
Quick!

110
00:06:12,167 --> 00:06:13,267
What? Go ahead!

111
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:14,233
Pull your gun...

112
00:06:15,733 --> 00:06:16,467
What?

113
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:17,533
Close the gate.

114
00:06:20,133 --> 00:06:21,133
Let Amo in.

115
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:26,433
Close the door.

116
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:30,167
Watch over there!

117
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,267
Amo!

118
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:35,167
What do you want?

119
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:35,933
Juice?

120
00:06:36,067 --> 00:06:37,867
Coffee? Soft drinks?

121
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:38,733
Orange?

122
00:06:38,867 --> 00:06:39,667
Banana?

123
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:41,000
I'm fine, thank you.

124
00:06:41,167 --> 00:06:41,900
Amo...

125
00:06:42,033 --> 00:06:43,633
Amo, let's take a picture.

126
00:06:43,767 --> 00:06:46,700
- Yes, of course! Go ahead, Amo.
- Go ahead, go ahead.

127
00:06:46,833 --> 00:06:47,733
You're so thick-faced,
aren't you?

128
00:06:47,867 --> 00:06:49,600
Daga, take a picture of us.

129
00:06:49,733 --> 00:06:51,567
Daga, take our picture,
take our picture.

130
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:52,400
Thank you.

131
00:06:53,433 --> 00:06:54,167
Okay.

132
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:58,400
Wacky, wacky. One, two, three.

133
00:06:58,533 --> 00:06:59,833
- Here. Thank you.
- Amo, thank you.

134
00:06:59,967 --> 00:07:01,033
Excuse me, Amo.

135
00:07:04,933 --> 00:07:08,033
Thank you,
for agreeing to talk to us.

136
00:07:09,267 --> 00:07:11,100
All I want is to help.

137
00:07:14,733 --> 00:07:17,367
You can really help us
a lot, Amo,

138
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,600
because you will be our ace.

139
00:07:21,033 --> 00:07:23,367
We will take you hostage.

140
00:07:25,933 --> 00:07:27,800
Amo is impressive, isn't he?

141
00:07:27,933 --> 00:07:30,133
He interfered in the police
operation.

142
00:07:30,267 --> 00:07:33,700
If he gets hurt or a hostage
gets hurt,

143
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:35,667
we will get the flak.

144
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:37,467
Is that impressive?

145
00:07:46,067 --> 00:07:46,633
Daga,

146
00:07:48,167 --> 00:07:50,433
can I know your real name?

147
00:07:54,233 --> 00:07:55,467
Funny, right?

148
00:07:58,133 --> 00:07:59,467
Why, Amo?

149
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:02,133
Do you want us to be best
friends?

150
00:08:03,633 --> 00:08:07,633
No, I want to help you.

151
00:08:09,533 --> 00:08:10,933
You want to help us.

152
00:08:12,067 --> 00:08:15,733
Why don't you talk to your
police friends outside

153
00:08:15,867 --> 00:08:19,567
to give us what we want and help
us escape from here

154
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:21,000
before there's any trouble.

155
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:27,700
I'm sorry, Daga...

156
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:31,100
but what you want won't happen.

157
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:37,033
Let's talk first,

158
00:08:37,167 --> 00:08:38,567
for the sake of all of you.

159
00:08:38,700 --> 00:08:43,700
Do you think what you're doing
is worth it

160
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:45,367
in exchange for your lives?

161
00:08:50,433 --> 00:08:51,100
Sir,

162
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:53,700
thank you earlier.

163
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:55,000
If you hadn't come,

164
00:08:55,167 --> 00:08:57,100
something might have happened
to the mother and son?

165
00:08:57,233 --> 00:08:59,600
You, what you did was solid too.

166
00:08:59,733 --> 00:09:02,500
You almost lost your life
just to save them.

167
00:09:03,967 --> 00:09:05,300
Not everyone will do that.

168
00:09:12,133 --> 00:09:14,200
I know what you're doing now,
Amo.

169
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:19,767
Did you think you could convince
me through a guilt trip?

170
00:09:22,167 --> 00:09:25,767
I know all of you actors
and politicians very well.

171
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:28,700
You're all the same.

172
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,367
You're all liars.

173
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:34,100
All you do is lead people on.

174
00:09:36,767 --> 00:09:38,667
You can't deny it, right?

175
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:40,300
Because it's true.

176
00:09:40,433 --> 00:09:45,833
That's because you haven't
experienced being poor like us.

177
00:09:47,933 --> 00:09:52,167
How will you know if you don't
listen to me?

178
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:53,567
Do you think...

179
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:58,067
it was you who made gangs
popular here in Calabari?

180
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:01,500
What are you talking about?

181
00:10:01,667 --> 00:10:04,800
Don't tell me you used
to be a gangster too.

182
00:10:04,933 --> 00:10:07,867
Yes, before.

183
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:12,200
That's why I understand you

184
00:10:12,333 --> 00:10:14,833
because we also had a hard life
back then.

185
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:40,300
Only a few of my friends know
what my life was like

186
00:10:40,433 --> 00:10:41,833
before I became an actor.

187
00:10:42,967 --> 00:10:44,300
I remember before,

188
00:10:44,433 --> 00:10:46,300
for me to gain the trust
of the gang,

189
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:48,933
they ordered me to steal.

190
00:10:50,100 --> 00:10:54,567
I also enjoyed the money
and the respect I got

191
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:56,467
because I became a gang member

192
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:57,433
but...

193
00:10:58,700 --> 00:11:02,933
my life got better
when I left the gang.

194
00:11:04,100 --> 00:11:08,067
Isn't that what we all want
to happen?

195
00:11:08,233 --> 00:11:10,367
Think carefully.

196
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:13,467
Maybe this is the turning
point of your life.

197
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:17,133
Make sure you make the right
decision.

198
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:21,500
Hey, stop that.

199
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:25,533
Don't believe this actor.

200
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:29,800
He's just saying that
to get what you want.

201
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:35,967
What if I slit your neck so you
will you take me seriously?

202
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:41,233
What if I slit your neck so you
will you take me seriously?

203
00:11:43,033 --> 00:11:46,600
It's your choice if you
want to hurt me.

204
00:11:47,667 --> 00:11:51,800
But this will be the end of all
of you.

205
00:11:51,933 --> 00:11:55,600
Don't you want to go home
to your family?

206
00:11:57,000 --> 00:12:00,533
Don't you want to see
your friends again?

207
00:12:01,767 --> 00:12:03,233
That's the same thing!

208
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:05,833
We'll be locked up too.

209
00:12:06,733 --> 00:12:08,833
We'll also rot in the group.

210
00:12:10,333 --> 00:12:11,967
So what's the point?

211
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:14,767
If that's the case,
let's just all die!

212
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:16,833
You're only saying that

213
00:12:16,967 --> 00:12:20,367
because you think you have
no other option.

214
00:12:23,867 --> 00:12:26,233
Do you think we want
to be like this?

215
00:12:26,367 --> 00:12:28,167
Do you think we want to steal?

216
00:12:28,300 --> 00:12:30,900
Do you think we don't want
a normal life?

217
00:12:31,033 --> 00:12:34,100
Those who have jobs, those who
can eat three times a day,

218
00:12:34,233 --> 00:12:37,100
those who have a livelihood
for our families?

219
00:12:38,267 --> 00:12:39,733
But no.

220
00:12:39,867 --> 00:12:42,133
It's a rotten system,

221
00:12:42,267 --> 00:12:45,267
especially for poor people
like us.

222
00:12:46,933 --> 00:12:49,467
Let's just say the system
is rotten,

223
00:12:49,633 --> 00:12:53,933
but can you change it
if you're in prison?

224
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:58,567
What about your family?

225
00:12:58,700 --> 00:13:00,033
What about your child?

226
00:13:01,333 --> 00:13:04,667
Daga, trust me.

227
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:06,067
Let us go,

228
00:13:07,333 --> 00:13:08,333
and I promise you,

229
00:13:08,467 --> 00:13:12,267
I'll do everything I can
to reduce your sentence.

230
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:15,367
And when you get out...

231
00:13:17,533 --> 00:13:19,133
you can start over.

232
00:13:21,533 --> 00:13:23,133
I'll give you a job.

233
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:27,233
How will we know you're not
fooling us?

234
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:29,200
Okay,

235
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:31,600
let's do this.

236
00:13:32,633 --> 00:13:35,700
If you don't want to give up,
don't.

237
00:13:35,833 --> 00:13:42,133
But Daga, please,
can you let them go?

238
00:13:42,267 --> 00:13:43,900
Just take me as a hostage.

239
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,367
Are you stupid?

240
00:13:48,233 --> 00:13:50,433
You're not related to them.

241
00:13:52,333 --> 00:13:53,233
Come here.

242
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:57,900
Would you give your life
to someone you don't know?

243
00:13:58,067 --> 00:14:03,400
Daga, not for them
but for all of you.

244
00:14:04,567 --> 00:14:08,100
All I want is to help you
change.

245
00:14:08,733 --> 00:14:12,300
Daga, there's still hope.

246
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:31,233
They will surrender!

247
00:14:36,667 --> 00:14:37,833
Amo!

248
00:14:39,167 --> 00:14:49,133
- Amo! Amo!
- Amo! Amo!

249
00:14:51,133 --> 00:14:52,500
Don't hurt them, okay?

250
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:55,033
Don't hurt them.

251
00:14:55,767 --> 00:14:59,200
- Amo! Amo!
- Amo! Amo!

252
00:14:59,333 --> 00:15:01,967
You won't regret your decision,
Daga.

253
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:09,100
Sir.

254
00:15:09,233 --> 00:15:10,433
My only request Major,

255
00:15:10,567 --> 00:15:13,867
I hope Daga and his companions
won't get hurt.

256
00:15:15,300 --> 00:15:17,000
From now on,
they're my responsibility.

257
00:15:18,067 --> 00:15:19,467
Okay, Sir Amo.

258
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:20,900
Thank you very much.

259
00:15:28,100 --> 00:15:28,833
I'll go ahead.

260
00:15:28,967 --> 00:15:30,033
Be careful.

261
00:15:31,967 --> 00:15:41,933
- Amo! Amo!
- Amo! Amo!

262
00:15:50,833 --> 00:15:51,833
How are you?

263
00:15:52,367 --> 00:15:54,000
I don't know.

264
00:15:54,133 --> 00:15:55,933
I'm really sorry.

265
00:15:56,067 --> 00:15:57,767
No, no, no.

266
00:15:58,133 --> 00:16:00,600
You don't need to be sorry,
my child.

267
00:16:00,733 --> 00:16:04,900
I just can't shake this feeling
that at any moment,

268
00:16:05,033 --> 00:16:06,233
this could happen again.

269
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:09,067
Don't you worry.

270
00:16:09,233 --> 00:16:11,733
It will never happen again.

271
00:16:11,867 --> 00:16:14,567
Mark my words, okay?

272
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:22,200
Daddy, do you think the lead
from the poison of the kidnapper

273
00:16:22,333 --> 00:16:26,300
who took me Will help the police
in finding the real mastermind?

274
00:16:26,433 --> 00:16:29,733
Of course, my child,
but it will take time.

275
00:16:29,867 --> 00:16:33,833
Trust me, Faye,
we will make him pay, okay?

276
00:16:33,967 --> 00:16:34,867
Promise?

277
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:36,233
Promise.

278
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:45,233
- Dad, you have to see this.
- Glen?

279
00:16:47,967 --> 00:16:49,867
Explosive news!

280
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:53,600
The hostage-taking
in Barangay Sta. Fe,

281
00:16:53,733 --> 00:16:58,133
filmed by gang members while
negotiating with

282
00:16:58,267 --> 00:17:00,267
Mayoral Candidate Victor "Amo"
Santiago, is now going viral.

283
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:02,533
Oh my.

284
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:06,333
It's very entertaining.

285
00:17:06,467 --> 00:17:09,167
It's becoming very
interesting.

286
00:17:25,567 --> 00:17:27,100
Have some coffee first.

287
00:17:27,233 --> 00:17:28,733
Thank you, Sir.

288
00:17:28,867 --> 00:17:32,200
Seriously, I still can't
believe all that happened.

289
00:17:32,333 --> 00:17:35,233
What Amo did was
on another level.

290
00:17:35,367 --> 00:17:39,600
I hope his connection to our
cases is just a coincidence.

291
00:17:39,733 --> 00:17:42,000
That's not good, Enriquez.

292
00:17:42,133 --> 00:17:43,067
Which one, Sir?

293
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:45,167
When you have wishful thinking,

294
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:48,000
that's where your bias in the
investigation comes in.

295
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:50,633
So if I were you,

296
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:55,233
let go of those feelings

297
00:17:55,367 --> 00:17:58,067
so that your eyes can be open
to everything.

298
00:17:58,200 --> 00:18:00,700
Besides, we don't have any
evidence against him yet.

299
00:18:03,233 --> 00:18:04,567
Miss Beautiful.

300
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:08,900
Thank you.

301
00:18:09,033 --> 00:18:11,100
Okay, thank you.
We'll take care of this.

302
00:18:20,100 --> 00:18:21,667
Daga...

303
00:18:21,833 --> 00:18:23,967
We just have a question for you.

304
00:18:24,100 --> 00:18:28,233
We just want to know what
started the gang war.

305
00:18:30,667 --> 00:18:33,067
It's nothing, Boss Chief.
It was just a fight among kids.

306
00:18:37,567 --> 00:18:39,033
Boss Chief,
can I ask a question?

307
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:41,800
Can we vote even if we're in
jail?

308
00:18:43,900 --> 00:18:45,700
Of course.

309
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:48,600
As long as you're not convicted,
you can still vote.

310
00:18:49,633 --> 00:18:50,833
Why did you ask?

311
00:18:52,267 --> 00:18:53,300
Good.

312
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:56,933
Because we want to vote for Amo.

313
00:18:57,100 --> 00:18:58,600
Because he's so kind.

314
00:18:58,733 --> 00:19:00,100
I hope he wins.

315
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:07,900
<i> Thank you and you agreed.</i>

316
00:19:08,033 --> 00:19:09,367
<i> Let me make it clear, okay?</i>

317
00:19:10,733 --> 00:19:14,700
<i>You want me to steal the trophy
to cause trouble.</i>

318
00:19:14,833 --> 00:19:16,933
<i>Am I understanding it correctly?</i>

319
00:19:17,067 --> 00:19:18,200
<i> Yes, Daga.</i>

320
00:19:18,333 --> 00:19:20,967
<i>We'll get into a rumble after
you steal the trophy.</i>

321
00:19:21,633 --> 00:19:24,800
<i>Then we'll take hostages,
then you'll fix it,</i>

322
00:19:26,067 --> 00:19:28,900
<i>and then you'll pay us
200,000 pesos.</i>

323
00:19:30,733 --> 00:19:32,033
<i> Wait, isn't that too little?</i>

324
00:19:32,167 --> 00:19:33,267
<i> We'll go to jail.</i>

325
00:19:34,467 --> 00:19:35,733
<i> It's like this.</i>

326
00:19:36,167 --> 00:19:40,900
<i>The trophy you will steal
contains P250,000</i>

327
00:19:41,033 --> 00:19:43,733
<i>plus the P200,000
that I'll give you.</i>

328
00:19:43,867 --> 00:19:45,500
<i> That's a lot for your group.</i>

329
00:19:45,633 --> 00:19:50,000
<i>Just act well,
and I'll take care of it.</i>

330
00:20:02,933 --> 00:20:04,033
Sir,

331
00:20:04,167 --> 00:20:07,767
thank you very much for advising
me on how to investigate.

332
00:20:07,900 --> 00:20:09,733
You know that's my goal,

333
00:20:09,867 --> 00:20:12,000
to be part of the Investigation
Group.

334
00:20:13,267 --> 00:20:15,967
In that case,
don't listen to me anymore.

335
00:20:17,033 --> 00:20:17,567
Sir.

336
00:20:19,300 --> 00:20:22,633
But I still want to investigate
Amo's connection.

337
00:20:23,967 --> 00:20:26,333
But it seems unlikely
that it will happen because...

338
00:20:26,467 --> 00:20:28,467
because of what happened,

339
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:31,800
I might have a hard time asking
Chief for his blessing again.

340
00:20:34,067 --> 00:20:35,967
That's just how Chief is.

341
00:20:36,133 --> 00:20:41,867
You need to get his attention
and find solid evidence,

342
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:45,100
not just based on coincidence.

343
00:20:45,233 --> 00:20:47,600
Sir, I don't know how to
proceed.

344
00:20:47,733 --> 00:20:49,933
Because I'm still in the...

345
00:20:52,100 --> 00:20:57,033
Why are the crimes that happened
in Amo's old movie connected?

346
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:01,033
To find the answers,

347
00:21:01,167 --> 00:21:04,933
you have to be willing
to change the questions.

348
00:21:05,067 --> 00:21:07,267
That's how it is when you
investigate.

349
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:12,300
The questions develop as you get
closer to the truth.

350
00:21:19,333 --> 00:21:20,600
I'm sorry, Sophia.

351
00:21:22,167 --> 00:21:23,367
I don't get it.

352
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:28,067
Don't people see what Victor
is doing to me?

353
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:31,333
He is destroying me?
He wants to be a hero!

354
00:21:31,467 --> 00:21:35,967
Well, if you think that Victor
is capable of doing such things,

355
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:38,300
then I suggest you tread
carefully.

356
00:21:38,433 --> 00:21:40,200
No, no! I'm sorry. Look!

357
00:21:40,333 --> 00:21:42,033
Look at the reactions
of netizens!

358
00:21:46,633 --> 00:21:49,800
Victor's drama is effective.

359
00:21:54,333 --> 00:21:55,667
Why are you laughing?

360
00:21:56,833 --> 00:22:01,000
It just amuses me that after
all this time in politics,

361
00:22:01,133 --> 00:22:05,133
it seems like you've only just
found a worthy opponent.

362
00:22:05,633 --> 00:22:09,300
My advice, Joaquin,
take the fight seriously.

363
00:22:09,433 --> 00:22:13,633
Just don't let your emotions get
the better of you.

364
00:22:16,167 --> 00:22:20,233
- Ma'am, Sir, snack time!
- Hey, perfect timing.

365
00:22:20,367 --> 00:22:21,467
What's in there?

366
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:23,300
Of course, lumpia.

367
00:22:23,433 --> 00:22:24,833
The question is, what flavor?

368
00:22:24,967 --> 00:22:26,800
I have some here,
special ube cheese,

369
00:22:26,933 --> 00:22:28,167
- I'll order two.
- Shanghai.

370
00:22:28,300 --> 00:22:29,233
You, Enriquez, do you want one?

371
00:22:29,367 --> 00:22:30,567
No, Sir, I'm fine.

372
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:31,600
Okay, two.

373
00:22:31,733 --> 00:22:32,933
Okay?

374
00:22:33,067 --> 00:22:34,000
Thank you.

375
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:36,100
Amo!

376
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:39,400
Amo!

377
00:22:40,967 --> 00:22:41,633
Good Evening.

378
00:22:41,767 --> 00:22:42,600
Good Evening to all of you.

379
00:22:44,133 --> 00:22:45,867
Amo, can I take a picture
with you?

380
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:46,400
And...

381
00:22:47,933 --> 00:22:50,200
is it okay for me to go live
when you're here

382
00:22:50,367 --> 00:22:51,800
so I can promote my merchandise?

383
00:22:51,933 --> 00:22:52,933
Oh my, don't do it.

384
00:22:53,067 --> 00:22:55,467
Maybe our countrymen will think
I'm trying to brag.

385
00:22:55,600 --> 00:23:00,167
I just want to thank our police
officers.

386
00:23:00,300 --> 00:23:04,033
That's okay, Amo, that's okay.
I'll go live.

387
00:23:06,100 --> 00:23:09,933
Good evening.

388
00:23:10,067 --> 00:23:11,633
Excuse me!

389
00:23:11,767 --> 00:23:15,233
This is the friend of Amo's son!

390
00:23:15,367 --> 00:23:16,767
Take another picture Amo,

391
00:23:16,900 --> 00:23:20,267
Amo, you know, what you did
earlier was so solid.

392
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:24,300
Don't mention it.
What you did was more solid.

393
00:23:24,467 --> 00:23:25,600
Thank you very much.

394
00:23:26,700 --> 00:23:29,200
Sir Victor, good evening.

395
00:23:29,333 --> 00:23:30,900
What can I do for you?

396
00:23:31,033 --> 00:23:34,433
Major Flores, meet,
Attorney Nuevo.

397
00:23:34,567 --> 00:23:36,467
He's the one who'll be handling
Daga's case.

398
00:23:36,600 --> 00:23:40,133
You know, free of charge.
He's our friend.

399
00:23:40,267 --> 00:23:41,000
Good evening, Attorney.

400
00:23:41,133 --> 00:23:42,333
Good evening, Major Flores.

401
00:23:42,467 --> 00:23:43,333
Amo...

402
00:23:43,467 --> 00:23:44,967
Is his services free?

403
00:23:45,100 --> 00:23:46,100
Of course.

404
00:23:46,233 --> 00:23:49,633
If you're given the chance
to help Amo's causes,

405
00:23:49,767 --> 00:23:50,700
you better take it.

406
00:23:52,367 --> 00:23:54,733
Attorney,
you'll take care of them.

407
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:59,667
Just make sure that Daga will
get what we agreed on.

408
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:01,433
You can count on it, Amo.

409
00:24:01,567 --> 00:24:04,033
Sir, maybe we can talk
to them for a moment.

410
00:24:04,167 --> 00:24:04,900
Yes, Attorney.

411
00:24:05,033 --> 00:24:07,300
Noble, please accompany
Attorney.

412
00:24:07,433 --> 00:24:08,033
Yes, Sir.

413
00:24:08,167 --> 00:24:09,200
Attorney, let's go.

414
00:24:13,833 --> 00:24:15,233
Sir Víctor,

415
00:24:15,367 --> 00:24:19,733
a sincere thank you from all
of us here at Station 12.

416
00:24:21,233 --> 00:24:22,733
Major, that's nothing.

417
00:24:22,867 --> 00:24:27,467
By the way, I apologize for
interfering with your operation.

418
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:29,033
But for me,

419
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:33,633
we really should give credit
to the first responders

420
00:24:33,767 --> 00:24:35,167
to the riot.

421
00:24:35,300 --> 00:24:39,300
It's them Sir Sergeant Enriquez
and Lieutenant Conde.

422
00:24:39,433 --> 00:24:41,700
Sergeant, Conde.

423
00:24:47,133 --> 00:24:48,000
Conde!

424
00:25:11,200 --> 00:25:13,267
What's Victor doing here?

425
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:15,700
You take care of the Daga's
families.

426
00:25:15,833 --> 00:25:17,000
Loud and clear, Amo.

427
00:25:17,133 --> 00:25:18,533
Loud and clear.

428
00:25:18,667 --> 00:25:20,867
You have a day with me too,
Victor.

429
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:22,167
When?

430
00:25:22,300 --> 00:25:25,233
You're looking for someone to
buy poison on the black market.

431
00:25:25,367 --> 00:25:26,300
We've found a contact.

432
00:25:26,433 --> 00:25:27,400
Just be careful, Boss.

433
00:25:27,533 --> 00:25:29,533
This is a dangerous world
you're about to enter.

434
00:25:29,667 --> 00:25:30,567
Look at this.

435
00:25:30,700 --> 00:25:32,733
Don't Amo and Lieutenant Conde
look alike?

436
00:25:32,867 --> 00:25:34,700
Yes, they look alike.

437
00:25:34,833 --> 00:25:35,600
Could it be that....

438
00:25:35,767 --> 00:25:37,067
- What, Ma'am?
- Are they related?

439
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:38,000
That's my hunch.

440
00:25:38,133 --> 00:25:39,467
We're not looking for trouble.

441
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:40,700
You're not going to get out
of here alive.

442
00:25:40,833 --> 00:25:41,933
Remember the rumor,

443
00:25:42,067 --> 00:25:45,200
when I told you that Amo
had an abandoned child?

444
00:25:45,333 --> 00:25:48,200
I'll just see where my intuition
takes me.

445
00:25:48,333 --> 00:25:49,800
Put your hands up!

446
00:25:49,933 --> 00:25:51,300
Put down your gun.

447
00:25:51,433 --> 00:25:52,700
We're not afraid of that.
